e Kanata location. Four or five TiE members attended, and it became clear t=
here is strong interest in AI learning sessions tailored for business users=
 with limited AI experience.

In my informal survey at that time, I found that most people were using Per=
plexity as just another search engine and many were unaware of its more adv=
anced capabilities. Few, if any, were strategically choosing the right tool=
s for the right tasks. People were defaulting to their "favorite" tool, usu=
ally based on cost, familiarity, or speed, regardless of fit. That=E2=80=99=
s when the idea emerged to offer an introductory session focused on helping=
 people understand the strengths, limitations, and best use cases for the m=
ost popular tools - ChatGPT, Gemini, Grok, Copilot and Perplexity.

