<div style=3D"direction:ltr;font-size:9.75pt">Good afternoon Tony,</div>
<p style=3D"direction:ltr;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">Thank you again=
 for your leadership and support. My apologies for being the last to provid=
e feedback<span style=3D"font-size:9.75pt">.
</span>I've been busy gathering insights from TiE members and our broader a=
udience in preparation for this session.</p>
<p style=3D"direction:ltr;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">Over the past f=
ew days, I=E2=80=99ve personally spoken with 15 TiE Ottawa members and char=
ter members to get their perspective on the first session in this AI series=
.
<span style=3D"font-size:9.75pt">As of now, w</span>e=E2=80=99re expecting =
over 40 attendees from TiE Ottawa alone<span style=3D"font-size:9.75pt">&nb=
sp;and</span>&nbsp;most identifying as novice or basic users of AI tools. O=
ne participant even requested to bring their 14-year-old,
 who is keenly interested in the topic. Another shared how they chose to in=
tegrate Grok into their product stack specifically because of the
<span style=3D"font-size:9.75pt">founder Elon Musk.</span></p>
<p style=3D"direction:ltr;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">This entire con=
cept was inspired by the TIM-led session on Perplexity at the Kanata locati=
on. Four or five TiE members attended, and it became clear there is strong =
interest in AI learning sessions tailored
 for business users with limited AI experience.</p>
<p style=3D"direction:ltr;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">In my informal =
survey<span style=3D"font-size:9.75pt">&nbsp;at that time</span>, I found t=
hat most people were using Perplexity as just another search engine<span st=
yle=3D"font-size:9.75pt">&nbsp;</span>and many were
 unaware of its more advanced capabilities. Few, if any, were strategically=
 choosing the right tools for the right tasks. People were defaulting to th=
eir &quot;favorite&quot; tool, usually based on cost, familiarity, or speed=
, regardless of fit. That=E2=80=99s when the idea
 emerged to offer an introductory session focused on helping people underst=
and the strengths, limitations, and best use cases for the most popular too=
ls<span style=3D"font-size:9.75pt">&nbsp;-
</span>ChatGPT, Gemini, Grok, <span style=3D"font-size:9.75pt">Copilot </sp=
an>and Perplexity.</p>
<p style=3D"direction:ltr;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">The expectation=
 from attendees is to walk away with three or four actionable takeaways tha=
t help them use these tools more effectively in their day-to-day work. This=
 session is meant to set the foundation
 for future, more focused sessions (e.g., <span style=3D"font-size:9.75pt">=
effective
</span>prompt engineering, vertical-specific AI for startups, etc.).</p>
<p style=3D"direction:ltr;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">Based on the au=
dience feedback, I=E2=80=99d like to suggest the following enhancements tha=
t could strengthen the session's impact:</p>
<ul style=3D"direction:ltr">
<li>
<p role=3D"presentation" style=3D"direction:ltr;margin-top:0px;margin-botto=
m:0px"><b>Ensure the session remains practical and example-driven.</b></p>
</li><li>
<p role=3D"presentation" style=3D"direction:ltr;margin-top:0px;margin-botto=
m:0px"><b>Consider these content areas to enhance value:</b></p>
</li><ul style=3D"direction:ltr">
<li>
<p role=3D"presentation" style=3D"direction:ltr;margin-top:0px;margin-botto=
m:0px">A high-level comparison of the most popular AI tools<span style=3D"f=
ont-size:9.75pt">&nbsp;that includes
</span>their strengths <span style=3D"font-size:9.75pt">(</span>and<span st=
yle=3D"font-size:9.75pt">&nbsp;maybe
</span>weaknesses<span style=3D"font-size:9.75pt">)</span></p>
</li><li>
<p role=3D"presentation" style=3D"direction:ltr;margin-top:0px;margin-botto=
m:0px">Simple techniques to improve usage (e.g., better prompts, as<span st=
yle=3D"font-size:9.75pt">&nbsp;its
</span>already included<span style=3D"font-size:9.75pt">&nbsp;in the slides=
</span>)<span style=3D"font-size:9.75pt">&nbsp;</span></p>
</li><li>
